# bug106_heterogeneous_list_test.zbr — BUG-106 verification.
#
# Before: [1, "two", 3] silently typechecked (RHS .unknown).
# After:  TC walks elements, picks first non-abstract as anchor, errors
#         at the offending element span if subsequent elements aren't
#         mutually isAssignable.
#
# Numeric mixes like [1, 2.0] should still pass because int/float are
# mutually isAssignable in Zebra (the "untyped numeric literal" principle).

def main()
    var xs = [1, "two", 3]
    print xs
